New Records: De'Aaron Fox scored 109 points over a two-game span, breaking the franchise record previously held by DeMarcus Cousins
Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox scored 49 points to lead the Kings to a 121-117 victory over the Jazz
Others: Kevin Huerter had 18 points, and Trey Lyles added 17 for the Kings. Lauri Markkanen had 25 points, Keyonte George scored 19 and Collin Sexton added 18 for the Jazz. Jordan Clarkson had 17 off the bench for Utah.
